net.ashwork.functionality.throwable.abstracts.operator

Interface AbstractThrowingOperator2<T,H extends AbstractThrowingFunction2.Handler<T,T,T>>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the operands and result of the operator
    H - the type of the handler to safely call the operator
    All Superinterfaces:
    AbstractThrowingFunction2<T,T,T,H>, AbstractThrowingFunctionN<T,H>, AbstractThrowingOperatorN<T,H>, net.ashwork.functionality.partial.Arity, net.ashwork.functionality.partial.ResultChainable<T>, net.ashwork.functionality.partial.ResultChainableResult<T>, ThrowableHandler<H,net.ashwork.functionality.FunctionN<T>>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ThrowingOperator2<T>

    @InheritOnly
public interface AbstractThrowingOperator2<T,H extends AbstractThrowingFunction2.Handler<T,T,T>>
extends AbstractThrowingOperatorN<T,H>, AbstractThrowingFunction2<T,T,T,H>
    Represents an operation that accepts two operands and produces a result of the same type as its operands. This is the two-arity specialization of AbstractThrowingOperatorN. This is a specialization of AbstractThrowingFunction2 where the operands and result are of the same type. This is the throwing variation of Operator2.
    Since:
    1.0.0
    See Also:
    AbstractThrowingOperatorN, AbstractThrowingFunction2, Operator2
    API Note:
    This is an abstract operator and should not be used directly. It should instead be called by one of its subtypes.
